  ./h1_fetch.py https://example.com
- The script prints the text content of the first <h1> or an error message to stderr.

Here's a small Go HTTP server that implements GET /hello?name=<name> and returns JSON like {"greeting":"Hello, <name>!"}, defaulting to "world" when name is absent.

```go
package main

import (
	"encoding/json"
	"log"
	"net/http"
)

type Response struct {
	Greeting string `json:"greeting"`
}

func helloHandler(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {
	if r.Method != http.MethodGet {
		http.Error(w, "Method not allowed", http.StatusMethodNotAllowed)
		return
	}

	name := r.URL.Query().Get("name")
	if name == "" {
